-- BMW Dealership Workers in China Strike Over Bonuses, Business Herald Says
-- Bloomberg News
-- 2010-06-22T23:31:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-22/workers-strike-at-bmw-dealership-in-northeast-china-on-bonuses-21st-says.html

          
          
             Workers at Bayerische Motoren Werke
AG’s dealership in the northeast Chinese city of Dalian went on
strike to protest “several hundreds of thousands yuan” of
unpaid bonuses, the 21st Century Business Herald reported.  
 No one was available for immediate comment when calls were
placed to BMW in Germany. Calls to the automaker’s service
center in China and the dealership, Dalian Yanbao Automobile,
went unanswered.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Jian Guo Jiang in Shanghai at 
 jjiang@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  


        